product.product_name: μHB MICRO HOMOGENIZER
product.description: The Omni Micro Homogenizer is a hand-held battery powered rotor-stator homogenizer designed for use inside or outside of a laboratory setting. The Micro homogenizer is powered by a 12 volt lithium ion battery that provides operating speeds from 5,000 to 30,000 rpm for rapid homogenization of samples in volumes from 0.20 mL to 100 mL. It is an ideal solution for field based homogenization procedures involving the processing of tissues or soft plant material.

product.product_name: Omni Mixer Homogenizer
product.description: Since 1956 the Omni Mixer Homogenizer has been synonymous with laboratory homogenizers. The Omni Mixer Homogenizer is a powerful 600 watt homogenizer that is compatible with a wide range of generator probes, blade assemblies and sealed containers to offer the perfect mix of dependability, versatility and power. The Omni mixer is ideally suited for homogenizing, blending and creating emulsions.

product.product_name: Generator Probe Adapter
product.description: Adapter is required for all Mixer Style Homogenizer Product Line generator probes. (One adapter is included with each Omni Mixer, Omni Macro, and Omni Macro-ES)

product.product_name: Quick Connect Coupling Assembly
product.description: The Quick Connect Assembly makes your Omni Mixer homogenizers even more convenient to use. The QCA is easy to install on your existing unit. It comes standard on the Omni Macro-ES and Omni Max. To use, attach a QCA adapter to your chamber assembly or generator probe. Next, slide the adapter in the QCA Slider assembly and a retaining ring positions into place for a secure hold. To disconnect, merely slide the ring upward and the processing accessory is conveniently released.

product.product_name: Quick Connect Coupling
product.description: The Quick Connect Assembly (QCA) makes your Omni Mixer Series homogenizer even more convenient to use. The QCA is easy to install on your existing unit. It comes standard on the Omni Macro-ES and Omni Max. To use, attach a Quick Connect Adapter (not included) to your chamber assembly or generator probe. Next, slide the adapter in the Quick Connect Coupling and a retaining ring positions into place for a secure hold. To disconnect, merely slide the ring upward and the processing accessory is conveniently released.

product.product_name: Vessel Restraint Disk
